Candor Corpus Analyses

Jamie Reilly, Ginny Ulichney, Ben Sacks

September 2023

We will be analyzing alignment across six dimensions as functions of age and age differences between speakers engaged in unscripted dyads: valence; trust; arousal; concreteness; word length (letters); word frequency (lg). Load dat from public github respository called reillylab_data.

Prep summary data

Creates summary dataframes collapsing across exchanges so that each dyad has one score for each dimension by unique combinations of participant and dyad (since one participant could have particpated in more than one dyad)

CONTRAST II:

AUC ~ Age-Differences

co-varied for sex, race, edu differences; first run scatterplot and examine linearity beteen AUC and age_diff – group by dimension and event_id

Correlation of Spearman Correlations ~ Age_Diff

Each dyad has one spearman correlation reflecting how strongly the partner pair moved together. We will the strength of this relationshop between how tightly coupled their responses are (in sync) with age difference between speakers. {r. fig.width=8, fig.height=10} #isolate all the spearman Rho vars per dyad for each dimension spearlong <- aucspear %>% pivot_longer(cols=c(20,22,24, 26, 28, 30), names_to = "dimension", values_to = "SpearmanRho_By_Dyad") %>% data.frame() spearlong$dimension <- as.factor(spearlong$dimension) spearSmall <- spearlong %>% select(dimension, event_id, SpearmanRho_By_Dyad, age_diff) %>% data.frame() spearman_sumDAT <- spearSmall %>% group_by(dimension, event_id) %>% dplyr::summarize_at(c("SpearmanRho_By_Dyad", "age_diff"), mean) %>% ungroup() %>% data.frame() str(spearman_sumDAT) spearplot <- ggplot(spearman_sumDAT, aes(age_diff, SpearmanRho_By_Dyad)) + geom_point(color="gray", shape = 2, size = .5, alpha = 0.3) + xlab("Age Difference") + ylab("AUC (alignment)") + geom_smooth(method = "loess", color = "red", fill="red") + jamie.theme + ggtitle("Bivariate Relations Alignment Spearman Rho ~ Age Difference") + facet_wrap(~dimension) print(spearplot)

Real vs. Random Dyad AUC contrasts

Density plots for AUC distributions for real dyads vs. randomly generated language transcripts by all dimensions

auc_fake <- aucspear %>%
    pivot_longer(1:6, names_to = "dimension", values_to = "AUC_randomdyads") %>%
    data.frame()
auc_fake_sumDAT <- auc_fake %>%
    select(dimension, event_id, AUC_randomdyads) %>%
    group_by(dimension, event_id) %>%
    dplyr::summarize_at("AUC_randomdyads", mean) %>%
    data.frame()
auc_fake_sumDAT$dimension <- as.factor(auc_fake_sumDAT$dimension)
auc_Both <- full_join(auc_sumDAT, auc_fake_sumDAT, by = c("dimension", "event_id"))
auc_Both$dimension <- as.factor(auc_Both$dimension)
auc_Both <- auc_Both %>%
    pivot_longer(cols = c("AUC_rating", "AUC_randomdyads"), names_to = "which_auc",
        values_to = "AUC") %>%
    data.frame()
auc_Both$which_auc <- as.factor(auc_Both$which_auc)
# Density plats AUC random to structured
col.vec <- c("goldenrod2", "blue")
auc_plots <- ggplot(auc_Both, aes(x = AUC, fill = which_auc)) + geom_density(alpha = 0.5,
    colour = "white") + scale_fill_manual(values = col.vec) + xlab("AUC (rand or real") +
    ylab("Density") + jamie.theme + ggtitle("AUC (alignment) Real vs. Simulated Conversations") +
    facet_wrap(~dimension, ncol = 2)
print(auc_plots)

Linear Mixed Effects Models: AUC by dimension predicted by age difference

Organize data

Select variables of interest, mean center independent variables for modeling

# joining covariates to wide df
covars <- SumDat_All %>%
    dplyr::select(c("event_id", "speaker_names_raw", "edu_diff", "sex_diff", "race_diff")) %>%
    distinct()
auc_lme_df <- left_join(auc_sumDAT, covars, by = c("event_id"))

# mean center continuous independent vars
auc_lme_df$age_diff <- as.vector(scale(auc_lme_df$age_diff, center = T, scale = F))
auc_lme_df$edu_diff <- as.vector(scale(auc_lme_df$edu_diff, center = T, scale = F))

# create dfs by dimension
trust_df <- subset(auc_lme_df, dimension == "auc_aff_trust")
val_df <- subset(auc_lme_df, dimension == "auc_aff_valence")
nletter_df <- subset(auc_lme_df, dimension == "auc_lex_letter_count_raw")
wordfreq_df <- subset(auc_lme_df, dimension == "auc_lex_wordfreqlg10_raw")
arousal_df <- subset(auc_lme_df, dimension == "auc_sem_arousal")
concrete_df <- subset(auc_lme_df, dimension == "auc_sem_concreteness")
